model.name: Kwang2003 - The influence of RKIP on the ERK signaling pathway

body.div: Kwang2003 - The influence of RKIP on the ERK signaling pathway

div.p: This model is described in the article:

div.a: Mathematical Modeling of the Influence of RKIP on the ERK Signaling Pathway

div.div: Kwang-Hyun Cho, Sung-Young Shin, Hyun-Woo Kim, Olaf Wolkenhauer, Brian McFerran and Walter Kolch
Computational Methods in Systems Biology: First International Workshop, CMSB 2003 Rovereto, Italy, February 24Ã¢??26, 2003 Proceedings

div.p: This paper investigates the influence of the Raf Kinase Inhibitor Pro- tein (RKIP) on the Extracellular signal Regulated Kinase (ERK) signaling pathway through mathematical modeling and simulation. Using nonlinear ordi- nary differential equations to represent biochemical reactions in the pathway, we suggest a technique for parameter estimation, utilizing time series data of proteins involved in the signaling pathway. The mathematical model allows the simulation the sensitivity of the ERK pathway to variations of initial RKIP and ERK-PP (phosphorylated ERK) concentrations along with time. Throughout the simulation study, we can qualitatively validate the proposed mathematical model compared with experimental results.
